#### Ciclo 1.2 — GREEN: Implementar merge policy configurable

Modificar `oxidize-pdf-core/src/pipeline/hybrid_chunking.rs`:

1. Anadir variant al config:

```rust
/// Policy for which adjacent element types can be merged.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum MergePolicy {
    /// Only merge Paragraph+Paragraph and ListItem+ListItem (legacy behavior).
    SameTypeOnly,
    /// Merge any adjacent non-structural elements (Paragraph, ListItem, KeyValue).
    /// Titles, Tables, Images, and CodeBlocks always start a new chunk.
    AnyInlineContent,
}

pub struct HybridChunkConfig {
    pub max_tokens: usize,
    pub overlap_tokens: usize,
    pub merge_adjacent: bool,
    pub propagate_headings: bool,
    /// Default: MergePolicy::AnyInlineContent (Docling pattern).
    pub merge_policy: MergePolicy,
}
```

2. Reemplazar `same_merge_group(a, b)` con logica basada en `merge_policy`:

```rust
fn can_merge_elements(a: &Element, b: &Element, policy: &MergePolicy) -> bool {
    match policy {
        MergePolicy::SameTypeOnly => matches!(
            (a, b),
            (Element::Paragraph(_), Element::Paragraph(_))
                | (Element::ListItem(_), Element::ListItem(_))
        ),
        MergePolicy::AnyInlineContent => {
            is_inline_element(a) && is_inline_element(b)
        }
    }
}

fn is_inline_element(e: &Element) -> bool {
    matches!(e,
        Element::Paragraph(_) | Element::ListItem(_) | Element::KeyValue(_)
    )
}
```

3. Actualizar `Default` para `HybridChunkConfig` para usar `MergePolicy::AnyInlineContent`.

4. Actualizar el test existente `test_no_merge_different_element_types` en
   `hybrid_chunking_test.rs` — ese test espera que Title+Paragraph NO se mergeen,
   lo cual sigue siendo correcto con `AnyInlineContent` porque Title no es inline.
   El test `test_list_items_merge_with_list_items_not_paragraphs` espera que
   ListItem y Paragraph NO se mergeen — ese test **deberara actualizarse** para
   reflejar la nueva politica o marcarse como `SameTypeOnly`.

